# 🌐 Networking Theory

## Network Ports

Network ports allow multiple services to communicate over a network.

Each service typically listens on a specific port number.

---

# Common Ports

| Service | Port |
|----------|------|
| SSH | 22 |
| HTTP | 80 |
| HTTPS | 443 |
| DNS | 53 |
| SMTP | 25 |

---

# Check Listening Ports

Command:

```bash
ss -tuln
```

Purpose:

Displays:

- Listening ports
- Protocols
- Local addresses
- Active network services

