# Real World Scenario

## Situation

A user reports:

"I cannot connect to the Linux server using SSH."

Instead of restarting the server immediately, the administrator first checks:

```bash
systemctl status ssh
```

The SSH service is running.

Next, the administrator investigates:

```bash
journalctl -u ssh
```

The logs reveal repeated authentication failures caused by incorrect credentials.

The administrator confirms the issue with the user rather than restarting the server unnecessarily.

This saves time and prevents unnecessary downtime.

